Database Administrator/SQL Programmer needed for a Plaintiff’s Law Firm located Dallas, Texas. We are looking for reliable, smart, motivated, goal-driven candidates who are team players with a positive and optimistic attitude who are interested in new challenges and seeking more efficient ways to improve projects.

Duties and skills needed will include, but not limited to:
Creating and editing SQL queries and workflows to assist with work assignments and projects;
Working with IT and other programmers for the betterment of the team;
Database administration and software design;
Using probing questions to identify needs or information to move projects to a conclusion;
Maintaining and improving quality results from large data;
Recommending improved processes;
Meeting productivity standards and ensures that team goals are exceeded;
Updating job knowledge by learning new procedures;
Enjoys working in a high-pace environment with multiple bosses;
Demonstrable enthusiasm and knowledge of SQL programming and software design;
Goals & quotas motivate you;
Bringing issues to the attention of your fellow IT team and attorney(s); and
Willingness to ask for help and give help to others.

The ideal candidate will have:
2+ years of SQL programming for an office environment;
Microsoft Power BI experience a plus;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Multi-tasking abilities;
Strong leadership skills;
Exceptional mathematic and problem-solving skills;
Confident, assertive, flexible and adaptable to change;
Ability to multi-task and remain calm under stress;
Strong logic skills, verbal communication, listening skills, and excellent SQL and workflow skills;
Energetic, quick learner, and flexible;
Manages multiple projects with multiple teams;
Organized and detail oriented and exhibits sound and fair judgment;
Identifies additional tasks to be completed and can approximately estimate the time to perform the tasks;
Reviewing & editing existing database and query performance, and understanding when to optimize code as to not delay a project.
Entry Level/Full-time, may consider part-time depending on schedule and qualifications

The purpose of this class within the organization is to provide Geographic Information System (GIS) support functions including planned and emergency maintenance of GIS databases and implementation of new products and procedures; analyze emerging technology and make recommendations for increased network/system services and capabilities; assist with support of other software and systems using GIS technology.


ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:

Maintains GIS enterprise databases;
Installs and maintains GIS software including operating systems, databases, servers, and applications;
Supports multiple networks and client/server applications and software packages;
Designs optimal end-user solutions for justified automation requirements using best practices for client server technology;
Coordinates with Information Technology personnel, including End User Support,, Systems, and Applications Programming in the use and maintenance of GIS systems, software, and data.
Performs related work as assigned.


QUALIFICATIONS:

Requires a Bachelor's Degree in geography, GIS, MIS, or a related field, plus three years of GIS related experience, or any combination of relevant education and experience.


KNOWLEDGE AND ABILITIES:


Knowledge of:
Advanced knowledge of Geographic Information Systems (GIS) software and relational databases and mapping and cartographic principles;
Working knowledge of Oracle, SQL, ESRI ArcGIS, FME, MS Office, including Access, particularly involving integrations with other systems;
Knowledge of Esri Versioned Workflows, ArcGIS Online, Esri Web Developer, ArcFM, and Python and other GIS related programming languages is a plus;
Data conversion and migration concepts and procedures;
Experience with municipal government generally and/or governmental utility systems is welcome, but not required
Ability to:
Plan, design, implement, configure, administer, operate and maintain a Geographic Information System (GIS) for a municipal government, including water, wastewater and stormwater utilities;
Analyze complex technical data and deliver solutions within given deadlines;
Provide technical leadership in the development and maintenance of electric utility GIS data models, data standards and systems integration;
Develop, implement and enforce QA/QC procedures;
Import and export data to and from a GIS;
Communicate effectively orally and in writing.
Physical Requirements:
Continuously lift and carry up to 10 pounds, and occasionally lift and carry up to 25 pounds;
Ability to occasionally report at non-standard hours and under extreme weather conditions for emergency response;
Frequently stand and walk during the shift;
Occasionally climb stairs and other inclined surfaces;
Occasionally bend and kneel during the shift;
Frequently flex upper trunk forward at the waist and partially at the knees;
Push and pull objects;
Occasionally rotate upper trunk to the left or right while sitting or standing. • Place arms above, at, or below shoulder height.
